OL,3,CParents urge council to keep
OL,4,C'community hub' local school open
OL,6,FFor parents like Sharon Currie, the
OL,7,Fschool has been a part of her life
OL,8,Fsince she herself was a child.
OL,10,FShe attended it for her primary and
OL,11,Fsecondary education, and now her
OL,12,Fchildren do too. "It's a big part of
OL,13,Fthe community," she explained.
OL,15,F"The well-being of my children is the
OL,16,Fmost important thing here, so I
OL,17,Fwouldn't be able to send them to
OL,18,Fanother school because they would not
OL,19,Fwant to leave Dalry school. They want
OL,20,Fto continue there education here."
